COMMITTEE REPORT
Mr. President: The Senate Committee on Education and Career
Development, to which was referred Senate Bill No. 78, has had the
same under consideration and begs leave to report the same back to the
Senate with the recommendation that said bill be AMENDED as
follows:
Page 2, line 21, after "must" insert "be stored away and
inaccessible to a student throughout the school day.".
Page 2, delete lines 22 through 26.
Page 2, line 36, delete "a physician's directive;" and insert "an order
provided by a health care provider who is licensed in Indiana;".
and when so amended that said bill do pass.
(Reference is to SB 78 as introduced.)
RAATZ, Chairperson
Committee Vote: Yeas 12, Nays 1.
